  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The dough is stiff and barely comes together into a log; that is correct. Biscotti have no butter or oil, which is what makes them last so long and become so dry. The key moment is the slicing: do it while the log is still warm (not hot), cutting at a slight diagonal to get long, even slices. Cut too cold and the slices shatter. The second bake drives out the last moisture; 15 minutes each side is usually enough, but ovens vary."
          }
        ]
      },
